modules.description: This module implements a runtime for executing YOCaml operations on Unix systems, providing functions for file system manipulation, logging, time measurement, and process execution. It works with paths, strings, and Unix-specific data like timestamps and process exit codes. Concrete use cases include reading and writing files, checking file existence, creating directories, hashing content, and running external programs with custom success checks.

This module runs YOCaml programs on Unix systems, providing `run` to execute and `serve` to re-run programs on file changes, with options for logging and error handling. It works with paths, integers, and formatting functions, enabling static site serving and file system operations. Concrete use cases include building and rebuilding websites, validating file structures, and handling Unix process execution with custom error reporting.
